{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1909", "title": "Off-highway vehicle: emergency response situation.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Off-highwayvehicle", "emergencyresponsesituation"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Under existing law, generally a motor vehicle may not be driven upon a highway unless it is registered. However, off-highway motor vehicles issued an identification plate or device may cross highways under specified conditions, including, among others, a peace officer in an emergency response situation.\n\nThis bill would similarly authorize first responders, as defined, to operate or drive an off-highway vehicle upon a highway to provide emergency response services or while performing official departmental duties."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Department of Motor Vehicles."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1909"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-12", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 15.", "date": "2026-02-13", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on TRANS.", "date": "2026-03-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on TRANS.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee chair, with author's amendments: Amend, and re-refer to Com. on TRANS. Read second time and amended.", "date": "2026-03-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["amendment-introduction", "amendment-passage", "reading-1", "reading-2"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Re-ref